{
  "name": "AI Hiring - Historical Outlook Scanner(PRODUCTION)",
  "nodes": [
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 📧 AI Hiring — Historical Outlook Scanner\n\n**Purpose:** One-time scan of ALL existing Outlook inbox emails with resume attachments. Processes emails that arrived before the real-time Outlook Monitor was set up.\n\n**How to run:** Click 'Execute Workflow' manually.\nScans every email matching resume keywords, skips duplicates, sends new resumes to parser.\n\n**Search filter used:** subject or body contains: resume OR cv OR curriculum\n",
        "height": 260,
        "width": 380,
        "color": 6
      },
      "id": "8a1b8669-83e6-4405-809f-72c244cc2a74",
      "name": "📋 Info",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -896,
        240
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## ⚠️ BEFORE RUNNING\n\n1. Replace OUTLOOK_CREDENTIAL_ID in Microsoft Outlook nodes\n2. Resume Parser workflow must be **Active**\n3. Uses `ol_` hash prefix — same as Outlook Monitor\n   → Already-processed emails will be skipped automatically\n4. Duplicate branch loops back to loop node (no Sheets write = no quota hit)\n",
        "height": 220,
        "width": 380,
        "color": 3
      },
      "id": "dd61d153-dc96-4da7-81e7-466c6ac4c7cc",
      "name": "⚠️ Setup",
